# v0.4.0 Multi-Project CF Library and Parallel-Section Build

Date: 2026-06-03

## Overview

Two major features added on top of v0.3.0 baseline. Both are gate-passing and fully wired
into the existing quality gate suite.

---

## Feature 1: Multi-Project Client-First Library System

### Problem

Every Webflow project has different CF class values (colors, spacing, typography tokens).
Previously there was no way to store, look up, or sync a per-project class library.
The global `knowledge-base/client-first-class-map.json` covers CF methodology but not
project-specific token values.

### Solution

Per-project library directories keyed by Webflow site ID, with a registry index and
Figma → library → Webflow sync pipeline.

### Files Created

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `tools/library_resolver.py` | Shared util: load registry, resolve/load library, register project, scaffold library dir, update last-synced. |
| `knowledge-base/libraries/registry.json` | Multi-project index (`{ "version": "1.0", "projects": [] }`). |
| `agentic/schemas/project-library.schema.json` | JSON Schema 2020-12 for per-project CF library (classes map with figma_token, cf_category, webflow_property, value). |
| `agentic/schemas/figma-token-map.schema.json` | JSON Schema 2020-12 for Figma variable → CF class name mapping. |
| `agentic/schemas/library-registry.schema.json` | JSON Schema 2020-12 for `registry.json`. |
| `scripts/gates/validate_project_library.py` | Gate: validates library JSON, token-map JSON, cross-checks class ↔ token coverage, changelog non-empty when classes exist. |
| `agentic/prompts/generate-cf-library.md` | LLM prompt template with naming rules (color vars → 3 classes, px÷16→rem, etc.) for Figma MCP → library generation. |
| `scripts/update_library_from_figma.py` | CLI: prints step-by-step instructions for LLM to call Figma MCP and generate/update library. |
| `scripts/sync_library_to_webflow.py` | CLI: loads library and prints ordered `style_tool` payloads for LLM to execute via Webflow MCP. |

### Files Modified

| File | Change |
|---|---|
| `scripts/init_workspace.py` | Added `--webflow-site-id` and `--figma-file-id` args; writes both to `meta.json`; auto-scaffolds library dir and registers project in registry when site-id provided. |
| `agentic/schemas/meta.schema.json` | Added optional `figmaFileId` and `webflowSiteId` fields. |
| `scripts/gates/run_quality_gate.py` | Auto-runs `validate_project_library` and `validate_build_contract` when `workspace/meta.json` contains `webflowSiteId`. |
| `agentic/knowledge/client-first-library.md` | Added "Multi-Project Library Workflow" section: registry, per-project dirs, how agents use `library_resolver.py`. |

### Library Directory Structure Per Project

```
knowledge-base/libraries/{webflow_site_id}/
  client-first-library.json   <- CF class → CSS property source of truth
  figma-token-map.json        <- Figma variable → CF class name mapping
  changelog.json              <- Audit trail of every class value change
```

---

## Feature 2: Parallel-Section Webflow Build Workflow

### Problem

Phase 2 (Webflow build) was single-operator and serial. For pages with many sections,
this is slow. Parallel subagent builds are blocked by a class-naming race: two agents
could invent the same class name with different values.

### Solution

HTML-contract-driven parallel build with strict phase split and apply-only subagents:

1. **Parent agent** reads Figma → emits ONE HTML contract (all sections, final CF class names).
   This serial authorship is the only place class names are decided.
2. **Phase 2A (serial, parent):** create new classes on Webflow + register into per-project library;
   create N section container elements in order → capture `parent_node_id` per section.
3. **Phase 2B (parallel):** spawn N `section-builder` subagents, each scoped to one `parent_node_id`.
   Subagents are apply-only — they recreate the HTML contract via native ops, never create classes.

HTML is an intermediate build contract, never a push payload (`whtml_builder` stays forbidden).

### Files Created

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `agentic/schemas/subagent-task.schema.json` | Handoff contract for section-builder: section_id, parent_node_id, html_contract, cf_classes, site_id, page_id, mcp_352, mode (const: "apply_only"). |
| `.claude/agents/section-builder.md` | Apply-only subagent role: scope = one section subtree under parent_node_id; forbidden = class creation, whtml_builder, writes outside subtree. |
| `.claude/skills/parallel-section-build/SKILL.md` | Parent orchestration skill: Phase 2A (class+container setup) → Phase 2B (spawn subagents). Includes concurrency-degradation note. |
| `.claude/skills/parallel-section-build/references/README.md` | Scaffold dir (required by validate_skills.py). |
| `.claude/skills/parallel-section-build/scripts/README.md` | Scaffold dir. |
| `.claude/skills/parallel-section-build/assets/README.md` | Scaffold dir. |
| `scripts/gates/validate_build_contract.py` | Gate: validates blueprint sections have html_contract + cf_classes; every referenced class exists in library or new_classes; no duplicate class names with conflicting definitions (naming-race guard). |

### Files Modified

| File | Change |
|---|---|
| `agentic/schemas/blueprint.schema.json` | Sections items support: section_id, html_contract, target_parent_node_id, cf_classes. Page-level `new_classes` array with required name/cf_category/webflow_property/value/reason fields. |
| `agentic/schemas/state.schema.json` | Optional `subagent_id` and `parent_node_id` fields on log entries. |
| `agentic/schemas/phase-state.schema.json` | Enum extended: `phase_2a_class_setup`, `phase_2b_parallel_section_build`. |
| `agentic/orchestration/sop.md` | Phase 2 split into 2A (serial class+container setup) and 2B (parallel section subagents). |
